# Workframe release triggers

**Before dogfood sync, docker restart on MyBusiness, publish, or install-gate: read** `d:/ab/.cursor/skills/workframe-release/SKILL.md` **first.**

## Hard stops

- No `robocopy /MIR` or full-tree copy into `../MyBusiness` or any install with `workframe-api/data/`.
- No touching `MyBusiness/workframe-api/data/` without user explicit OK.
- Wipe/reset only via `scripts/workframe/sign-off-install.ps1` or `reset-dogfood-docker.ps1 -Confirm` when user asks.
- Source only: `services/workframe-api/`, `apps/web/src/` — then build → sync-canonical → bundle per skill.

See also: workspace rule `workframe-release-triggers` (MyBusiness paths), `workframe-environments`, `workframe-installer-mirror`.
